Penangkapan Interpol

Seven people have been shot dead in an attack on a mosque in a village in north-eastern Kenya near the border with Somalia, officials have said.
Villagers told the BBC that 10 gunmen opened fire as people were leaving the mosque after early morning prayers. Five men were killed and then two women who heard shots and came to investigate were also shot dead.
The attack comes less than two weeks before elections in a region where security is a problem.
In the past year, the region has also been prone to attacks blamed on al-Qaeda-aligned Islamist militants in Somalia.
Tujuh orang tewas di tembak dalam satu serangan di sebuah masjid di sebuah desa di Kenya timur laut di dekat perbatasan dengan Somalia, tutur para pejabat.
