Andean glaciers face unprecedented threat
Sungai es Andes menghadapi ancaman
Goat cleared of eating greens
Kambing dibebaskan dari dakwaan makan tanaman

A new study has found that glaciers in the Andes have shrunk by as much as 50% over the past 40 years.
The research, published in the journal The Cryosphere, predicts many glaciers in the tropical Andes could melt away altogether.
The researchers blamed a 0.7 degrees rise in temperatures for what they called unprecedented glacier retreat.
The Chacaltaya glacier in the Bolivian Andes, once a ski resort, has already disappeared completely, according to some scientists.
Satu penelitian baru menunjukkan bahwa sungai es di pegunungan Andes menciut sebesar 50% dalam 40 tahun terakhir.
Penelitian yang diterbitkan di jurnal The Cryosphere memperkirakan banyak sungai es di pegunungan tropis Andes akan meleleh semuanya.
Para peneliti mengatakan suhu udara 0,7 drajat menyebabkan melelehnya gletser yang belum pernah terjadi sebelumnya.
Gletser Chacaltaya di pegunungan Andes Bolivia sempat menjadi resor ski namun sekarang telah meleleh, menurut sejumlah ilmuwan.

A magistrate in Australia has dismissed charges against a goat named Gary, booked by Sydney police for eating flowers outside the Museum of Contemporary Art.
Gary's owner, James Dezarnaulds, had decided to contest the $460 fine issued for damaging vegetation.
And magistrate Carolyn Barkell ruled that there was no evidence that Gary had gone to the museum with the intention of eating garden plants, nor that Mr Dezarnaulds had put the goat up to the deed.
The police had argued that Mr Dezarnaulds had acted recklessly in allowing a hungry goat approach the flower bed.
Pengadilan di Australia mencabut dakwaan atas seekor kambing yang bernama Gary, yang didenda polisi Sydney karena makan bunga di luar Museum Seni Kontemporer.
Pemilik Gary, James Dazamaulds, memutuskan untuk menentang denda $460 karena merusak tanaman.
Hakim Carolyn Barkell menetapkan tidak ada bukti bahwa Gary berjalan ke museum dengan tujuan makan tanaman. Dezarnaulds juga tidak membawa kambingnya untuk tujuan itu.
Polisi mengklaim Dezarnauld bertindak gegabah karena membiarkan kambingnya yang lapar mendekati rangkaian tanaman bunga.
