Native Canadians hold protests
Penduduk asli Kanada mengadakan protes
Clinton "concerned" for missing Laos activist
Clinton "prihatin" atas aktivis Laos yang hilang

Thousands of native Canadians have held a day of action across the country over their long-running demands for better living conditions for indigenous peoples.
Protestors caused a big traffic tailback at one of the busiest border crossings with the United States, blocked several other highways, and halted train services.
The Idle No More movement has galvanised many of Canada's one-point-two million aboriginals, who say their communities suffer from disproportionately high levels of unemployment, substance abuse and suicides.
Ribuan penduduk asli Kanada menggelar aksi selama satu hari di seluruh penjuru negeri terkait tuntutan lama menyangkut perbaikan taraf hidup bagi warga asli.
Pengunjuk rasa menyebabkan kemacetan lalu lintas di salah satu pelintasan perbatasan tersibuk dengan Amerika Serikat, memblokir sejumlah jalan bebas hambatan, dan menghentikan layanan kereta.
Gerakan Idle No More mempersatukan banyak dari 1,2 juta penduduk asli Kanada. Mereka mengatakan komunitas mereka menderita akibat tingkat pengangguran tinggi secara tidak proporsional, penyalahgunaan obat, dan bunuh diri.

The US Secretary of State Hillary Clinton has urged Laos to investigate the whereabouts of a prominent social activist who disappeared a month ago while driving home.
Security camera footage showed Sombath Somphone being taken away by unidentified men after he was stopped by police in the capital Vientiane.
The communist authorities in Laos say they don't know what's happened to him.
Mr Sombath had been advocating sustainable development and land rights for farmers.
Menteri Luar Negeri Amerika Serikat Hillary Clinton menyerukan kepada Laos untuk menyelidiki keberadaan aktivis sosial terkenal yang hilang satu bulan lalu ketika sedang mengemudi.
Rekaman kamera keamanan menunjukkan Sombath Somphone dibawa oleh orang-orang tidak dikenal setelah dicegat oleh polisi di ibukota Vientiane.
Pihak berwenang komunis di Laos mengatakan mereka tidak tahu apa yang terjadi padanya.
Sombath melakukan advokasi pembangunan berkelanjutan dan hak-hak tanah bagi petani.
