Eat less mackerel, UK told
Inggris diminta mengurangi makan ikan mackerel
France and Germany celebrate landmark treaty
Prancis dan Jerman merayakan traktat sangat penting

Fish-eaters in Britain are being warned that mackerel is no longer a sustainable choice.
A charity, the Marine Conservation Society, says it's being over-fished and should be eaten only occasionally.
Mackerel, endorsed by celebrity chefs, has become increasingly popular, amid a greater awareness of the potential health benefits of oily fish.
The charity suggests herring and sardines as alternatives.
British fishermen say mackerel stocks are healthy and the advice is premature.
Penggemar ikan di Inggris diperingatkan bahwa mackerel (semacam ikan kembung) tidak lagi menjadi pilihan berkelanjutan.
Lembaga amal Marine Conservation Society mengatakan mackerel ditangkap secara berlebihan dan seharusnya dikonsumsi kadang-kadang saja.
Mackerel, dengan dukungan kepala juru masak, semakin populer di tengah kesadaran lebih luas mengenai potensi manfaat ikan berminyak bagi kesehatan.
Lembaga amal mengusulkan ikan herring dan sardin sebagai alternatif.

The French President, Francois Hollande, has joined the German Chancellor, Angela Merkel, for a day of celebrations in Berlin, to mark half a century since their countries signed a landmark agreement. 
The Elysee treaty - signed in 1963 - sealed the friendship between the two former enemies after the Second World War.
The French and German parliaments will meet later for a joint session inside the Reichstag building in Berlin; hundreds of extra chairs are being put in for the visiting French deputies.
Presiden Prancis Francois Hollande bergabung bersama Kanselir Jerman Angela Merkel untuk menghadiri perayaan satu hari di Berlin guna menandai setengah abad sejak kedua negara menandatangani kesepakatan sangat penting.
Traktat Elysee, ditandatangani tahun 1963, menandai persahabatan antara dua bekas musuh setelah Perang Dunia Kedua.
Parlemen Prancis dan Jerman akan bertemu dalam sidang gabungan di gedung Reichstag di Berlin. Ratusan kursi tambahan disediakan untuk anggota parlemen Prancis yang sedang berkunjung.
