Tropical storm hit Phillippines
Tea workers burn boss to death
Badai tropis menghantam Filipina
Pekerja teh membakar majikan sampai mati

A tropical storm has killed at least four people in the central Philippines just weeks after a typhoon left hundreds dead. Three people died when a tree fell on their house in Samar province and at least one other person was killed by a landslide. The Philippine authorities said most people had taken precautions before the storm hit the central islands on Christmas Day following the devastation caused by Typhoon Bopha which killed hundreds people earlier this month.
Tea plantation workers in the northeastern Indian state of Assam have set fire to their boss's house, burning him and his wife to death. Reports say about700 workers, angry over a two-week dispute over accommodation, surrounded the owner's bungalow late on Wednesday and set it alight. The charred bodies of Mridul Kumar Bhattacharyya and his wife, Rita, were later found in the debris. Police have detained three workers in connection with the attack, at Kunapathar.



The charred bodies of Mridul Kumar Bhattacharyya and his wife, Rita, were later found in the debris.
Jenazah yang hangus dari Mridul Kumar Bhattacharyya dan istrinya, Rita, belakangan ditemukan di puing-puing.
Badai tropis telah menewaskan sedikitnya empat orang di Filipina tengah hanya sepekan setelah topan yang menyebabkan ratusan tewas. Tiga orang tewas ketika pohon jatuh ke rumah mereka di Provinsi Samar dan sedikitnya seorang lain tewas karena tanah longsor. Pihak berwenang Filipina mengatakan sebagian besar orang sudah berjaga-jaga sebelum badai menghantam kepulauan di bagian tengah pada Hari Natal setelah kehancuran yang diakibatkan Topan Bopha yang sebelumnya menewaskan ratusan orang pada bulan ini.
Para pekerja perkebunan teh di negara bagian India timur laut, Assam, menyulut api ke rumah majukan mereka, membakar dia dan istrinya hingga tewas. Laporan-laporan menyebutkan sekitar 700 pekerja, yang marah kerana sengketa selama dua pekan dalam soal akomodasi- mengepung rumah pemilik pada Rabu malam dan membakarnya. Jenazah yang hangus dari Mridul Kumar Bhattacharyya dan istrinya, Rita, belakangan ditemukan di puing-puing. Polisi sudah menangkap tiga pekerja sehubungan dengan serangan di Kunapathar itu.
