The Indian government says it's considering increasing the punishment for rape, after an attack that has left a bus passenger fighting for her life.
It has also promised more police patrols on routes frequented by women at night.
The woman was gang-raped as she travelled home from the cinema with a male friend in Delhi.
The two were then beaten, stripped and thrown out of the vehicle. Four people, including the bus driver, have been arrested.
The incident has caused outrage across India.
Pemerintah India mengatakan mereka mempertimbangkan memperberat hukuman kasus perkosaan, setelah kasus perkosaan membuat seorang penumpang bus berjuang untuk bertahan hidup.
Pemerintah juga berjanji mengerahkan lebih banyak polisi di rute-rute yang banyak dilalui kaum perempuan di malam hari.
Korban diperkosa beramai-ramai ketika ia pulang dari menonton bioskop bersama teman prianya.
Keduanya kemudian dipukuli, dilucuti pakaiannya, dan dikeluarkan dari kendaraan.
Empat orang, termasuk sopir bus telah ditangkap.
Insiden ini memicu kemarahan besar di seluruh India.



A United States judge has refused a request by the computing giant Apple to ban sales of smartphones made by its rival, Samsung.
Earlier this year, in the latest round of a legal battle between the two companies, a US jury awarded Apple damages after finding that Samsung had copied key features of Apple products.
But the judge, Lucy Koh, said Apple's patents covered only a small fraction of the features on Samsung smartphones.
Hakim di Amerika Serikat menolak permintaan raksasa komputer Apple agar penjualan telepon genggam pintar buatan pesaing Apple, Samsung, dilarang.
Sebelumnya tahun ini, dalam putaran terbaru sengketa hukum antara kedua perusahaan, juri di AS memutuskan Apple berhak mendapatkan ganti rugi setelah menyatakan bahwa Samsung meniru fitur-fitur penting produk Apple.
Namun hakim Lucy Koh mengatakan paten Apple hanya mencakup sebagian kecil fitur ponsel pintar Samsung.
