Nigerian printing company investigates lost notes
Pencetak uang Nigeria menyelidiki uang kertas yang hilang

Newly-released figures from last year's census in England and Wales show a big rise in the number of people living here who were born abroad. 
Over the past decade, there has been an increase of nearly two-thirds, to seven-and-a-half million.
The top five countries of birth were India, Poland, Pakistan, Ireland and Germany. 
Christians (in England and Wales) has fallen by four million since the previous census in two-thousand-and-one.
Fourteen million people said they had no religion -- nearly double the number last time.
Data baru hasil sensus tahun lalu di England dan Wales menunjukkan peningkatan besar jumlah warga yang tinggal di sini yang lahir di luar negeri.
Selama satu dekade terakhir, terdapat kenaikan hampir dua pertiga menjadi 7,5 juta orang.
Lima negara terbesar asal mereka adalah India, Polandia, Pakistan, Irlandia dan Jerman.
Jumlah pemeluk Kristen (di England dan Wales) turun sebanyak empat juta sejak sensus terakhir pada 2001.
Empat juta orang mengatakan mereka tidak mempunyai agama, hampir dua kali lipat dari jumlah pada sensus lalu.

The company that prints notes for the Central Bank of Nigeria is trying to find out how more than thirteen million dollars worth of new notes went missing.
The Nigeria Security Printing and Minting Company (NSPMC) has suspended its managing director and head of security while it carries out an investigation.
The anti-corruption body, Transparency International, ranks Nigeria as the thirty-fifth most corrupt country in the world, but the government disputes this.
Perusahaan yang mencetak uang kertas untuk Bank Sentral Nigeria berusaha mengetahui bagaimana uang kertas baru senilai hampir US$13 juta hilang.
Perusahaan Nigeria Security Printing and Minting Company (NSPMC) telah memberhentikan direktur pelaksana dan kepala keamanan sementara dilakukan penyelidikan.
Organisasi antikorupsi, Transparency International, menempatkan Nigeria di urutan ke-35 dalam daftar negara-negara yang paling korup di dunia, tetapi pemerintah membantahnya.
