Huge crowds swarmed central Wellington for the world premiere of Peter Jackson's The Hobbit.
A crowd of about a hundred-thousand people has turned out in the New Zealand capital, Wellington, for the world premiere of the film, The Hobbit. 
The movie is a prequel to the hugely successful trilogy, The Lord of the Rings, and is based on the 1937 children's novel by JRR Tolkien.
Fans cheered the director, Peter Jackson, and actors from the film at the screening.
Sekitar 100.000 orang datang ke ibukota Selandia Baru, Wellington, dalam rangka pemutaran perdana di dunia film The Hobbit.
Film ini merupakan lanjutan dari trilogi yang sukses, The Lord of the Rings, dan dibuat berdasarkan novel anak-anak karangan JRR Tolkien tahun 1937.
