Brazilian police find 15-metre drugs tunnel
Polisi Brasil temukan terowongan obat bius
Chinese man compensated after acquittal
Pria Cina dapat ganti rugi karena salah hukum

Police in the Brazilian city of Sao Paolo say they have discovered a tunnel used by drug traffickers to deliver cocaine to university students.
The fifteen-metre tunnel started at the home of a drug trafficker, led past a cocaine lab and ended near a wall between the University of Sao Paolo campus and a slum.
The traffickers exchanged drugs for money through a hole in the wall. The tunnel was discovered by chance when police were searching for suspects.
Polisi di kota Sao Paolo, Brasil, mengatakan mereka menemukan terowongan yang digunakan oleh para pedagang obat bius untuk menyalurkan kokain ke mahasiswa.
Terowongan sepanjang 15 meter itu berpangkal di kediaman seorang pedagang obat bius, melalui laboratorium kokain dan berakhir di dekat satu tembok antara kampus Universitas Sao Paolo dan satu daerah kumuh.
Para pedagang obat bius melakukan transaksi jual beli obat bius melalui lubang di tembok itu. Terowongan itu ditemukan secara tidak sengaja oleh polisi yang tengah mengejar tersangka.

A provincial court in China has awarded one of the country's highest compensation payouts - US$130.000- to a man who served 11 years in prison after being wrongfully convicted.
The thirty-nine-year-old former steel worker received a sentence of life imprisonment in 2000 for cheque fraud and was acquitted in 2010 on the grounds of insufficient evidence.
The supreme court in Guangdong province said he was being compensated for lack of personal freedom as well as psychological and emotional distress.
Pengadilan di propinsi Cina memberikan uang ganti rugi sebesar US$130.000 kepada seorang pria yang mendekam di penjara selama 11 tahun karena salah hukum.
Mantan pegawai industri baja berusia 39 tahun itu dihukum penjara seumur hidup tahun 2000 karena penggelapan uang dan dibebaskan tahun 2010 dengan alasan tidak ada bukti cukup.
Mahkamah Agung di propinsi Guandong mengatakan ia mendapat ganti rugi karena kehilangan kebebasan dan juga mengalami tekanan mental.
