Japanese car sales plunge in China
Penjualan mobil Jepang turun tajam di Cina
Railway Man' author dies

Japanese car companies have reported a sharp fall in sales to China because of tensions over disputed islands in the East China Sea.
Toyota, Honda and Suzuki said that sales fell by more than forty per cent in September, after anti-Japanese protests swept through Chinese cities.
Japanese car factories in China are reported to have slowed production because of the falling demand.
Some temporarily closed down after production lines were hit by vandalism and arson attacks.
Beberapa perusahaan mobil Jepang mengumumkan penurunan tajam penjualan di Cina karena ketegangan soal sengketa kepulauan di Laut Cina Timur.
Toyota, Honda, dan Suzuki mengatakan penjualan turun lebih 40% pada bulan September, setelah protes anti-Jepang melanda kota-kota di Cina.
Pabrik-pabrik mobil Jepang di Cina dilaporkan mengurangi produksi karena permintaan menurun.
Beberapa di antaranya tutup setelah muncul pengrusakan dan pembakaran di pabrik-pabrik tersebut.

A former British prisoner of war, whose memoir is being turned into a film starring the Hollywood actors Colin Firth and Nicole Kidman, has died.
Eric Lomax was captured by the Japanese in Singapore in 1942 and forced to work on the Thailand to Burma line, which became known as the "death railway" because of the brutal conditions under which it was built.
Mr Lomax later came to terms with his experience by meeting - and reconciling with - one of his Japanese captors, and writing a book, The Railway Man.
The film adaptation is expected to be released next year.
Mantan tawanan perang Inggris, yang perjalanan hidupnya diangkat menjadi film yang dibintangi aktor Hollywood Colin Firth dan Nicole Kidman, telah meninggal dunia.
Eric Lomax ditangkap Jepang di Singapura pada 1942 dan dipaksa bekerja membangun rel kereta antara Thailand dan Burma, yang kemudian terkenal dengan "rel maut" karena brutalnya kondisi yang harus dihadapi para pekerja.
Lomax kemudian bisa melepas kenangan buruknya dengan bertemu dan berdamai dengan orang-orang yang menangkapnya dan menulis buku, The Railway Man.
Film adaptasi diperkirakan akan diputar tahun depan.
