Abortion boat "blocked from Moroccan port"
Kapal aborsi "dilarang memasuki pelabuhan Maroko"
Hague calls for cyber hotlines

This ship offers women in Marocco medical abortions.
A Dutch ship which was heading for the coast of Morocco to offer women medical abortions has been prevented from entering port, according to the campaigners who sent it.
The group, Women on Waves, says the port of Smir has been completely closed and warships are blocking the harbour.
On Wednesday Morocco said the vessel had not been invited by the proper authorities, and was operating outside the law.
Moroccan legislation prevents abortion, except where the life of the mother is in danger. This was to have been the boat's first visit to a Muslim country.
Kapal Belanda yang menuju Maroko untuk menawarkan aborsi medis kepada para perempuan dilarang memasuki pelabuhan, menurut para pegiat yang mengirim kapal tersebut.
Kelompok Women on Waves mengatakan pelabuhan Smir ditutup total dan kapal-kapal perang ditempatkan di pelabuhan.
Pada hari Rabu Maroko mengatakan kapal itu tidak diundang oleh lembaga resmi dan beroperasi di luar hukum.
Undang-undang Maroko melarang aborsi, kecuali bila nyawa sang ibu terancam. Ini adalah kunjungan pertama kapal ke negara Muslim.

The British Foreign Secretary, William Hague, has said international hotlines need to be established to deal with new emergencies that might arise in cyberspace.
Mr Hague told a cybersecurity conference in Hungary that it had never been easier to become a cyber criminal, and that governments needed to communicate better to tackle the problem.
But he said the risks should not overshadow the benefits brought by the digital age - and stressed that greater state control of the internet was not the answer.
Menteri Luar Negeri Inggris, William Hague, mengatakan telepon khusus internasional perlu disediakan untuk menghadapi situasi darurat yang mungkin muncul di dunia maya.
Dalam konferensi keamanan dunia maya di Hungaria, Hague mengatakan dewasa ini sangat mudah menjadi penjahat maya dan berbagai pemerintah harus meningkatkan komunikasi untuk mengatasi masalah ini.
Namun ia mengatakan risiko yang timbul tidak semestinya mengurangi manfaat dari abad digital ini dan menekankan bahwa kontrol negara yang lebih besar bukan jawaban yang tepat.
