The Swedish furniture manufacturer Ikea has said it regrets that images of women are missing in the Saudi Arabian version of its catalogue.
A comparison with the Ikea catalogue available elsewhere in the world reveals that women have been airbrushed out of otherwise identical pictures.
Ikea said the removal of the images had been carried out by a franchisee and conflicted with the company's values.
Censorship of images of unveiled women in magazines and catalogues is common in Saudi Arabia, which follows a very conservative school of Islam.
Perusahaan furnitur Swedia IKEA mengatakan mereka menyesalkan penghapusan foto-foto wanita di katalog mereka untuk Arab Saudi.
Setelah dibandingkan dengan katalog serupa untuk negara-negara lain, terungkap bahwa foto-foto wanita di katalog Saudi dihapus.
IKEA mengatakan penghapusan foto-foto wanita dilakukan oleh perusahaan pemegang hak pemasaran mereka dan bertentangan dengan nilai-nilai perusahaan.
Sensor foto-foto wanita di majalah dan katalog biasa dilakukan di Saudi, negara yang menganut aliran Islam konservatif.
