The chairman of Google, Eric Schmidt, has urged North Korea to end its self-imposed isolation and allow its citizens to use the internet. Speaking after a visit to Pyongyang, he said North Korea would continue to lag economically unless it embraced internet freedom.
Mr Schmidt was part of a US delegation that included the former state governor, Bill Richardson.
They also urged North Korea to end nuclear and missile tests and ensure humane treatment for an American citizen under arrest in Pyongyang. Mr Richardson said they had failed to secure his release.
One in 16 North Koreans own a mobile phone, but North Korea still has some of the world's tightest restrictions on communications with the outside world.)
Ketua Google, Eric Schmidt, mendesak Korea Utara untuk menghentikan pengasingan diri-sendiri dan mengizinkan warganya untuk menggunakan internet.
Berbicara setelah berkunjung ke Pyongyang, dia mengatakan Korea Utara akan terus tertinggal secara ekonomi kecuali merangkul kebebasan internet.
