Australian teen survives inland taipan bite
Remaja Australia selamat dari gigitan ular taipan darat
Burma's speaker says reforms irreversible
Ketua Parlemen Burma mengatakan reformasi tidak bisa dibendung

An Australian teenager has survived a bite from the world's most venomous snake.
The seventeen-year-old was struck on the hand by an inland taipan -- one drop of whose venom is considered enough to kill a hundred people.
There's speculation it could have been an illegal pet. Australian doctors say rapid treatment with anti-toxins almost certainly saved the boy's life.
He's seriously ill in hospital. Inland taipans can grow up to two metres long, with twelve-millimetre fangs.
Seorang remaja Ausrtralia selamat dari gigitan ular paling berbisa di dunia.
Remaja berusia 17 tahun itu digigit di tangannya oleh ular taipan darat, setetes bisanya dianggap cukup untuk membunuh seratus orang.
Muncul spekulasi bahwa ular tersebut merupakan hewan piaraan ilegal. Para dokter Australia mengatakan pengobatan cepat dengan antitoksin hampir dipastikan menyelamatkan nyawa remaja laki-laki itu.
Dia sakit keras di rumah sakit. Ular taipan darat bisa mempunyai panjang sampai dua meter, dan 12 milimeter gigi taring.

The powerful speaker of the Burmese parliament has told the BBC that reforms in his country are irreversible. 
Shwe Mann said the goal remained to establish multi-party democracy and a market economy.
He said Burma's reformist leaders needed to learn from the past to help them serve the people better.
Shwe Mann was one of the leaders of the previous military government: he said the opposition leader Aung San Suu Kyi was not his enemy.
Ketua parlemen berpengaruh di Burma mengatakan kepada BBC bahwa reformasi di negaranya tidak bisa dibendung.
Shwe Mann mengatakan tujuan masih ditetapkan untuk membangun demokrasi multipartai dan ekonomi pasar.
Dia mengatakan para pemimpin reformis Burma perlu belajar dari masa lalu untuk membantu melayani rakyat secara lebih baik.
Shwe Mann merupakan salah seorang pemimpin dari pemerintah militer sebelumnya: dia mengatakan pemimpin oposisi Aung San Suu Kyi bukan musuhnya.
