Actor is suing the filmmaker
Aktris menuntut pembuat film
Two men killed by bear
Dua orang dibunuh beruang

One of the actors who appeared in an anti-Islamic video which prompted protests across the Muslim world, is suing the filmmaker for fraud and slander.
Cindy Lee Garcia is also asking a judge in California to force the video-sharing website, YouTube, to remove the film.
Ms Garcia said she and fellow actors were duped into thinking they were appearing in an adventure film set in ancient Egypt.
She said the film's anti-Islamic references were dubbed in afterwards and that the script contained no mention of the Prophet Mohammed. The film's Egyptian producer, Nakoula Basseley Nakoula, has gone into hiding.
Salah seorang aktris yang tampil dalam video anti-Islam yang memicu protes di negara-negara Islam, menuntut pembuat film karena penipuan dan fitnah.
Cindy Lee Garcia juga meminta seorang hakim di California memaksa situs berbagi video, YouTube, untuk mencabut film itu.
Gracia mengatakan dia dan rekan sesama aktor dikelabui untuk berpikir bahwa mereka tampil dalam sebuah film petualangan dengan tempat di Mesir kuno.
Dia mengatakan rujukan anti-Islam di film itu dimasukkan kemudian dan naskah tidak menyebut Nabi Muhammad. Pembuat film orang Mesir, Nakoula Basseley Nakoula, sudah lari bersembunyi.



The latest victim was attacked by an animal that had been injured by a poacher's trap.
Korban terbaru diserang oleh seekor hewan yang terluka akibat perangkap pemburu.
A 64 year old man has been killed by a bear in Romania. It's the second such death this week in the Carpathian mountains north of Bucharest.
The latest victim was attacked by an animal that had been injured by a poacher's trap.
Another bear that killed a 71 year old man in the same region last Saturday was later shot, and laboratory tests revealed that it had rabies. Romania is home to more than 4.000 -more than any other country in the European Union.
Seorang pria berusia 64 tahun dibunuh oleh seekor beruang di Rumania. Ini merupakan kematian kedua di pegunungan Carpathian di sebelah utara Bukares.
Korban terbaru diserang oleh seekor hewan yang terluka akibat perangkap pemburu.
Beruang lain, yang membunuh seorang pria 71 tahun di kawasan yang sama Sabtu lalu, belakangan ditembak dan uji laboratotium mengungkapkan hewan itu mengidap rabies.
Rumania merupakan tempat tinggal lebih dari 4.000 beruang -lebih banyak dibanding negara lain di Uni Eropa.
