Cape Town hippo to be darted
Kuda nil Cape Town akan dibius
South Korea typhoon kills at least nine
Topan Korea Selatan tewaskan sembilan orang

The days of freedom for a hippo who escaped from a nature reserve in Cape Town look set to end.
The city's environment department is planning to fire a dart at the animal and transport it to a new home. The animal has been touring the suburbs, eating lawns and shrubs, after 300 metres of the fence around the reserve were stolen.
The reserve's hippo herd is a major tourist attraction. Once it has been captured, the young animal will be transported to a new home in the Gondwana game reserve near Mossel Bay.
Hari-hari bebas seekor kuda nil yang lari dari kawasan perlindungan di Cape Town akan segera berakhir.
Departemen lingkungan kota itu merencanakan untuk membius binatang itu dan diangkut ke habitat barunya.
Kudal nil itu lari dan berkeliling luar kota Cape Town dan makan rumput serta semak belukar, setelah pagar seluas 300 meter di seputar kawasan lindung itu dicuri.
Kawasan lindung kuda nil itu merupakan atraksi turis. Begitu ditangkap, binatang itu akan diangkut ke habitat baru di kawasan lindung Gondwana di dekat Teluk Mossel.

Typhoon Bolaven has passed over South Korea, killing nine people and leaving ten others missing. 
In the capital Seoul the power supply to hundreds of thousands of homes and businesses was cut and bridges were forced to close.
The typhoon has now passed on into flood-prone North Korea - where several regions have already lost crops to heavy rains in the last few months.
Angin topan Bolaven melanda Korea Selatan, menewaskan sembilan orang dan sepuluh lainnya hilang.
Di ibukota Seoul, aliran listrik untuk ratusan ribu rumah dan kantor terputus sementara jembatan-jembatan terpaksa ditutup.
Angin topan itu kini telah mengarah ke Korea Utara. Sejumlah kawasan di negara itu mengalami gagal panen karena hujan lebat dalam beberapa bulan terakhir.
