A zoo in the Japanese capital, Tokyo, says one of its pandas has given birth.
It's the first time the zoo's natural breeding programme has been successful.
The two pandas -- a female called Shin Shin and a male called Ri Ri -- were leased from China last year and first appeared in public after the nuclear disaster at Fukishima.
Kebun binatang di ibukota Jepang, Tokyo, mengatakan salah satu pandanya telah melahirkan.
Inilah pertama kalinya program perkembangbiakan alami di kebun binatang membuahkan hasil.
Dua ekor pandang, panda betina bernama Shin Shin dan panda jantan bernama Ri Ri, dipinjam dari Cina tahun lalu dan pertama kali tampil di muka umum setelah bencana nuklir di Fukushima.
