A new survey says the Japanese capital, Tokyo, has become the most expensive city in the world for foreign staff to live in.
It's overtaken Luanda, the capital of Angola. The yen's rise against the dollar has pushed up the cost of living for workers paid in foreign currencies.
The Eurozone crisis has reduced costs in European cities, with Paris, Rome and Athens sliding down the ratings.
Survei baru menunjukkan bahwa ibukota Jepang, Tokyo, menjadi kota paling mahal di dunia bagi pekerja asing.
Tokyo mengambil alih posisi Luanda, ibukota Angola. Kenaikan nilai mata uang yen terhadap dolar meningkatkan biaya hidup pekerja asing yang digaji dalam mata uang-mata uang asing.
Krisis di zona euro mengurangi biaya hidup di kota-kota Eropa. Paris, Roma dan Athena turun peringkat.
