China dismisses new Iran sanction call
Cina menolak seruan sanksi baru terhadap Iran
Black rhino extinct in West Africa
Berita pertama tentang penolakan Cina atas usul sanksi baru terhadap Iran dan berita kedua tentang punahnya badak hitam di kawasan Afrika Barat.

A Chinese official said sanctions could not fundamentally resolve the issue.
China has dismissed calls for tougher sanctions on Iran in response to a UN report this week that's raised new concerns about Tehran's nuclear programme.
The Chinese foreign ministry said sanctions could not fundamentally resolve the issue and urged renewed diplomatic efforts.
Russia has also said it won't support new sanctions.
Both Britain and France have said fresh measures should be taken against Iran, partly in response to speculation that Israel is planning an imminent air strike on Iran's nuclear facilities.
Cina menolak seruan sanksi yang lebih keras terhadap Iran setelah PBB mengeluarkan laporan pekan ini yang kembali mengangkat kekhawatiran baru program nuklir Teheran.
Kementerian Luar Negeri Cina mengatakan sanksi tidak dapat menyelesaikan masalah dan mendesak dimulainya kembali berbagai upaya diplomasi.
Rusia juga mengatakan tidak akan mendukung sanksi baru.
Baik Inggris dan Prancis mengatakan harus ada tindakan untuk Iran, antara lain guna menanggapi spekulasi bahwa Israel merencanakan serangan udara terhadap fasiltias nuklir Iran.

Rhino horn is greatly prized in traditional medicines in East Asia.
The latest global assessment of threatened plant and animal species says that the black rhino has been poached into extinction in West Africa.
The International Union for Conservation of Nature also listed the northern white rhino of Central Africa as possibly extinct.
Rhino horn is greatly prized in traditional medicines in East Asia and as dagger handles in the Middle East.
The agency also classified a quarter of all mammals as at risk of extinction worldwide , along with five out of eight species of tuna.
Penelitian global terbaru tentang spesies tumbuhan dan hewan yang terancam menyebutkan badak hitam telah habis diburu di Afrika Barat.
Organisasi Internasional untuk Konservasi Alam juga mengatakan badak putih mungkin juga telah punah di Afrika Tengah.
Cula badak sangat dihargai sebagai obat tradisional di Asia Timur dan sebagai gagang pisau belati di Timur Tengah.
Organisasi ini juga mencatat seperempat mamalia menghadapi risiko punah di seluruh dunia, demikian juga dengan lima dari delapan spesies ikan tuna.
