Japan's politicians talk about nuclear restart
Para politisi Jepang membicarakan pengoperasian kembali nuklir
Berita pertama mengenai serangan roket di Israel dan berita kedua tentang pembangkit listrik tenaga nuklir di Jepang.

Israeli police say a rocket fired from Egypt hit the southern Israeli resort of Eilat during the night as thousands of people gather there for the Jewish holiday of Passover.
The authorities say nobody was injured and there was no damage done.
Rocket attacks on Israel from Egyptian soil are unusual - this is thought to be the first for more than a year.
Israel says Islamist militants have become active in the Sinai peninsula in Egypt since the overthrow of President Hosni Mubarak in February 2011.
Kepolisian Israel mengatakan sebuah roket yang ditembakkan dari Mesir mendarat di kawasan wisata Eilat, Israel selatan tadi malam ketika ribuan orang berkumpul di sana untuk merayakan festival Paskah Yahudi.
Pihak berwenang mengatakan tak seorang pun mengalami luka-luka dan tidak terjadi kerusakan.
