US storm leaves 12 dead
Badai di AS telan 12 korban jiwa
Australian army criticises 'repugnant' web comments
Berita pertama tentang badai di Amerika Serikat yang menyebabkan korban jiwa dan berita kedua tentang tentara Australia yang mengkritik anggota yang menulis komentar rasis di online.
At least twelve people have been killed by severe storms in the United States. Seventeen tornado sightings were reported across six states in the South and Mid West.
In Illinois witnesses described furniture being sucked out of hotel room windows. The governors of Kansas and Missouri have declared a state of emergency.
Paling tidak dua belas orang tewas akibat badai yang menerjang Amerika Serikat.
Tujuh belas angin topan dilaporkan di enam negara bagian di kawasan Selatan dan Barat Tengah Amerika.
Di Illinois, para saksi mata menggambarkan perabotan tersedot keluar dari jendela-jendela hotel. Gubernur Kansas dan Missouri menetapkan keadaan darurat.
The Australian Army says it will punish any serving members of the armed forces who posted sexist or racist remarks on a military-themed page on the social network site Facebook.
The army said comments left on the RAR Buddies group page made repugnant remarks about Muslims and women and that they were contrary to the army's values.
Hundreds of serving and former members of the military were members of the group, which has now closed. A BBC correspondent in Sydney said this is the latest in a series of scandals to hit the armed services in Australia.
Angkatan Darat Australia mengatakan akan menghukum anggota yang memasang komentar berbau rasis dan seksis di laman bertema militer di jejaring sosial Facebook.
Pihak AD mengatakan laman RAR Buddies memasang komentar kotor tentang Muslim dan wanita dan bahwa pendapat-pendapat itu bertentangan dengan nilai-nilai kemiliteran. Ratusan tentara dan mantan militer menjadi anggota laman yang kini telah ditutup itu.
Wartawan BBC di Sydney mengatakan insiden ini merupakan yang kesekian kali dari serangkaian skandal yang terjadi di angkatan bersenjata Australia.
