President of the Maldives resigns
Presiden Maladewa mengundurkan diri
Dickens
Dickens
Kita awali dengan berita mengenai pengunduran diri presiden Maladewa dan kemudian kita simak berita mengenai peringatan kelahiran penulis Inggris terkenal, Charles Dickens.

The president of the Maldives, Mohamed Nasheed, has resigned.
He made the announcement on national television following weeks of protest after he controversially ordered the arrest of the country's top criminal court judge, Justice Abdulla Mohamed.
Mr Nasheed accused the judge of favouring opposition politicians such as Maumoon Abdul Gayoom, the previous president of thirty years.
The vice president is expected to take over.
Presiden Maladewa Mohamed Nasheed telah mengundurkan diri.
Dia mengumumkan pengunduran diri lewat televisi nasional menyusul unjuk rasa selama berminggu-minggu setelah secara kontroversial dia memerintahkan penangkapan hakim tertinggi pengadilan pidana, Hakim Abdulla Mohamed.
Nasheed menuduh hakim mendukung para politisi oposisi seperti Maumoon Abdul Gayoom, mantan presiden yang berkuasa selama 30 tahun.
Wakil presiden diperkirakan akan mengambil alih jabatan.

The two-hundredth anniversary of the birth of Charles Dickens is being celebrated across the world today (Tuesday).
A ceremony will be held at his birthplace, Portsmouth on the south coast of England.
His works, such as 'David Copperfield', 'Oliver Twist' and 'Great Expectations', remain widely read and are regularly adapted for the screen.
He died in 1870 and was buried in Westminster Abbey in London, where Prince Charles will lay a wreath in the presence of what's likely to be the largest-ever gathering of the writer's descendants.
Dickens was a keen observer and his stories frequently portray the fate of ordinary people, often living in abject poverty and squalor through no fault of their own.
Peringatakan kelahiran ke-200 Charles Dickens dirayakan di seluruh penjuru dunia hari ini (Selasa).
Upacara akan diadakan di kota kelahirannya, Portsmouth, di pesisir selatan Inggris.
Karya-karyanya, seperti David Copperfield, Oliver Twist dan Great Expectations masih dibaca oleh banyak orang dan sering diadaptasi ke layar lebar.                     
Dia meninggal dunia pada 1870 dan dimakamkan di Westminster Abbey di London. Di tempat ini, Pangeran Charles akan meletakkan karangan bunga yang akan disaksikan oleh keturunan penulis tersebut dan pertemuan ini tampaknya akan menjadi pertemuan terbesar para keturunan Dickens.
Dickens adalah pengamat yang tajam dan cerita-ceritanya seringkali menggambarkan nasib rakyat biasa, mereka hidup dalam kondisi sangat miskin dan melarat bukan atas kesalahan mereka sendiri.
