Radioactive rice discovered in Japan
Beras mengandung radioaktif ditemukan di Jepang
Forbes publishes Africa rich list
Berita pertama tentang penemuan beras yang mengandung radioaktif di Fukushima dan berita kedua tentang daftar orang-orang terkaya di Afrika versi majalah Forbes.

The Japanese government said none of the rice had been sold.
Japan has banned shipments of rice from an area near the nuclear power station at Fukushima, which was damaged in an earthquake last March.
A sample of rice from a farm in Fukushima City, about 60 kilometres from the plant, was found to have unsafe levels of radioactive caesium.
The Japanese government said none of the rice had been sold.
A BBC correspondent in Japan says the case highlights the difficulty of tracking radiation, which has been spread by wind and rain since the Fukushima disaster.
Jepang melarang pengapalan beras dari satu kawasan di dekat Pembangkit Listrik Tenaga Nuklir Fukushima, yang rusak akibat gempa bumi Maret lalu.
Sampel beras dari satu daerah pertanian di Fukushima City, sekitar 60 kilometer dari PLTN, diketahui mengandung radioaktif sesium dengan kadar tidak lagi aman.
Pemerintah Jepang mengatakan beras tersebut belum terjual.
Wartawan BBC di Jepang mengatakan kasus ini menggarisbawahi sulitnya melacak radiasi, yang disebarkan oleh angin dan hujan sejak bencana PLTN Fukushima.

Egypt has the most billionaires in Africa, says Forbes.
Forbes Magazine has published its first list of Africa's richest people.
A Nigerian cement mogul, Aliko Dangote, who has a fortune of more than ten billion dollars topped the list.
Nicky Oppenheimer, the chairman of the South African diamond mine company, De Beers, came in at number two.
Forbes' list of the forty richest people in Africa put their combined wealth at nearly sixty-five billion dollars.
Egypt has the most billionaires on the continent, with seven coming from just two families, the Sawiris and Mansours.
Majalah Forbes untuk pertama kalinya menerbitkan daftar orang terkaya Afrika.
Pengusaha semen Nigeria, Aliko Dangote, yang memiliki kekayaan lebih dari US$10 miliar menempati urutan teratas.
Nicky Oppenheimer, presiden direktur perusahaan tambang berlian Afrika Selatan Dee Beers berada di tempat kedua.
Total kekayaan 40 orang terkaya Afrika versi Forbes mencapai hampir US$65 miliar.
Mesir memiliki miliuner terbanyak di Afrika, dengan memasukkan tujuh orang yang berasal dari dua keluarga, Sawiri dan Mansour.
